fields.value: Replication Data for: Wing wear reduces bumblebee flight performance  in a dynamic obstacle course

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This dataset supports the publication: Mountcastle AM, Alexander TM, Switzer CM, Combes SA. (in review) Wing wear reduces bumblebee flight performance  in a dynamic obstacle course. Biology Letters.

Each .csv file contains body center-of-mass tracking data for an individual flight trial of a bee in one of three treatment groups: INT, ASYM or SYM. The first three columns of data are the raw output from the DLTdv5 tracking software, and represent x,y,z body coordinates (in mm). The fourth column ('include-frame') indicates whether the row of data was included (value = 1) or excluded (value = 0) from the kinematic analysis. Excluded segments of data were associated with either body collisions or camera obstructions.
